sec.p:
The aim here was to find for each individual subject, rat or mouse, the values of the model M’s parameter set θ (here α and β) that best fit the data by maximizing the log-likelihood LL of the trial-by-trial sequence of proportions of time spent exploring object o1 relative to object o2, as observed in the experimental dataset D:




θopt=argmaxθ{log(P(D|M,θ))}


(4)





LLopt=maxθ{log(D|M,θ)}


(5)
